> We've tasted a whole lot of skewers in our day, but nothing compares to the flavor combo of rosemary, beef, and garlic in this recipe. And just when we thought it couldn't get any better, our expert chefs, Freida and Nate, tossed in some crisp green beans and juicy tomatoes. Needless to say, we're in love.

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the broiler, oven, or #grill{} to high. Soak the @wooden skewers{4} in a shallow #dish{} of water. Take the @butter{1%tablespoon} out of the fridge to allow it to come to room temperature. Peel and mince the @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Strip the @rosemary{1/4%ounce} of the sprigs, then finely chop the leaves (you'll want about 2 teaspoons). Halve the @lemon{1}. Trim the ends of the @green beans{6%ounces}.

Toss the @beef sirloin tips{8%ounces} in a #medium bowl{} with the rosemary, half the garlic, and a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}. Season generously with @salt{generous pinch} and @pepper{generous pinch}.

== Garlic Bread ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @butter{1%tablespoon} and as much remaining garlic as you like. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Halve the @ciabatta bread{1} and spread the butter onto the two halves.

== Charred Veggies ==

Toss the green beans and @heirloom grape tomatoes{4%ounces} on a #foil-lined baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Place the green beans and tomatoes under the broiler for ~{5-6%minutes}, until charred. Remove from oven and set aside. Squeeze the lemon halves over the #baking sheet{}, then tent with foil to keep warm.

== Beef Skewers ==

While the veggies broil, thread the beef onto the skewers and place onto another baking sheet. Broil ~{5-6%minutes}, until slightly charred.

== Broiled Garlic Ciabatta ==

Broil the garlic bread: With ~{3%minutes} to go on the beef skewers, place the ciabatta, butter-side up, on the same baking sheet. Broil ~{2-3%minutes}, until toasted. Cut into 4 slices. Serve the rosemary beef skewers with the green beans, tomatoes, and garlic ciabatta.